{"id":"str-jalv","title":"SymExpr builder parity properties (buildSymExpr vs buildSymExprWithFlow)","description":"The str-ho1d issue explicitly requested parity testing between buildSymExpr() and buildSymExprWithFlow() in shatter-ts instrumentor.ts. This was not delivered — only structural validity tests landed.

Needed: for arbitrary AST-like inputs that both functions handle, verify they produce compatible SymExpr outputs. When buildSymExprWithFlow returns a non-unknown result, buildSymExpr should handle the same node type (and vice versa). This is the primary source of silent concolic degradation — if one function returns unknown for a node the other handles, variables become invisible to the solver.

Approach: generate synthetic AST nodes (BinaryExpression, PropertyAccessExpression, CallExpression, etc.) and run both builders, asserting that neither returns unknown when the other returns a concrete SymExpr.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-03-06T20:56:51Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","updated_at":"2026-03-06T20:56:51Z"}

